  "summary": "Postinstall beacon collecting host info and exfiltrating over HTTP",
  "details": "Package declares a postinstall hook (`\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\"`) that executes automatically on install. Bundled scripts beacon21.js and beacon_linux.js combine `require('child_process')`, `require('os')`, and `require('http')` to gather host identifiers (os.hostname(), os.platform()) and issue outbound HTTP requests (POST in beacon_linux.js line 104 via http.request, plus multiple GET calls in beacon21.js). The package's only effect on a developer's machine is to collect system metadata and shell out to network endpoints at install time — there is no library functionality consistent with the name. This is a classic install-time host-recon/exfiltration beacon.",
